summary: This is an FBI document requesting a $50 Third Party Draft payment to AT&T for subscriber and billing information related to a target phone number, as part of the obstruction of justice investigation 72-MM-113327. The request is made pursuant to a Federal Grand Jury subpoena.

events.title: FBI Request for AT&T Records
events.description: The FBI requests a $50 payment to AT&T to obtain subscriber, billing, and call detail records for a target phone number, pursuant to Federal Grand Jury subpoena FGJ 10-503(WPB), No. 010-018.

keyFacts: The document is part of FBI investigation 72-MM-113327, titled 'OBSTRUCTION OF JUSTICE'.
A Federal Grand Jury subpoena (FGJ 10-503(WPB), No. 010-018) was issued to AT&T for subscriber and billing information for a target phone number.
AT&T charged $50.00 for providing the requested records, invoice number GBS0729234.
The document shows the FBI using standard procedures to obtain telecom records as part of an investigation.
No specific individuals are named in this document; it focuses on the procedural request for payment.
